  <header>
    <h1>Computer Ports — Full Catalog</h1>
  </header>

  <p style="color:#444;margin-top:12px">This catalog includes full-color images of computer ports (modern, legacy, enterprise, obscure). Images are hotlinked from Wikimedia Commons / public sources. Click the source link for license details.</p>

  <div class="topbar">
    <div class="chip">Includes: USB, Thunderbolt, VGA, HDMI, RJ45, DE-9, DB-25, SCSI, IDE/PATA, Molex, internal headers, legacy connectors</div>
    <div class="chip">All images hotlinked, free-licensed where possible</div>
  </div>

  <!-- Legacy & Enterprise -->
  <div class="section-title">Legacy & Enterprise — Serial / Parallel / SCSI / Storage</div>
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="thumb"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6b/Serialport.jpg" alt="DE-9 serial port"></div>
      <div class="meta">
        <h3>DE-9 (RS-232 serial)</h3>
        <p>9-pin D-sub serial port used for COM ports. <a class="source" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Serialport.jpg" target="_blank">Image source</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="thumb"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/45/DB-25_Parallel_Connector.svg" alt="DB-25 parallel"></div>
      <div class="meta">
        <h3>DB-25 (Parallel)</h3>
        <p>25-pin D-sub used for printers (LPT) or legacy serial. <a class="source" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:DB-25_Parallel_Connector.svg" target="_blank">Image source</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="thumb"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2f/SCSI_50pin.jpg" alt="SCSI 50-pin"></div>
      <div class="meta">
        <h3>SCSI 50-pin</h3>
        <p>Narrow SCSI connector used on older devices. <a class="source" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:SCSI_50pin.jpg" target="_blank">Image source</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="thumb"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/14/40pin_IDE_cable.JPG" alt="IDE 40-pin"></div>
      <div class="meta">
        <h3>IDE / PATA 40-pin</h3>
        <p>Ribbon cable interface for older drives. <a class="source" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:40pin_IDE_cable.JPG" target="_blank">Image source</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="thumb"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6f/Mini-Centronics_36_pin_with_Micro-Centronics_36_pin.jpg" alt="Centronics 36-pin"></div>
      <div class="meta">
        <h3>Centronics 36 / Micro-Ribbon</h3>
        <p>Legacy printer connector. <a class="source" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mini-Centronics_36_pin_with_Micro-Centronics_36_pin.jpg" target="_blank">Image source</a></p>
